  "prompt": "What are some good psychological thriller movies of 2015?",
  "response": "There were several notable psychological thriller movies released in 2015. Here are some of the most recognized ones:\n\n1. **Gone Girl** - Directed by David Fincher and based on Gillian Flynn's best-selling novel, this film follows the mysterious disappearance of a woman and the subsequent media frenzy and police investigation, exposing dark truths about her marriage.\n\n2. **The Gift** - Written and directed by Joel Edgerton, this film revolves around a married couple whose lives are disrupted by a former acquaintance from the husband's past who brings with him a series of troubling gifts and secrets.\n\n3. **Ex Machina** - Alex Garland's directorial debut delves into themes of artificial intelligence, consciousness, and manipulation through the story of a young programmer who is selected to participate in a groundbreaking experiment with a highly advanced AI.\n\n4. **Secret in Their Eyes** - This film, a remake of the Argentine film of the same name, follows an FBI investigator who revisits a cold case involving the murder of his daughter, uncovering deep-seated emotions and dark truths.\n\n5. **The Invitation** - Directed by Karyn Kusama, it focuses on a man attending a dinner party hosted by his ex-wife, where old memories and a sense of dread lead to unexpected and terrifying revelations.\n\n6. **The Look of Silence** - Although more of a documentary, this film by Joshua Oppenheimer is psychologically gripping as it follows a man confronting individuals involved in the Indonesian mass killings of 1965\u201366.\n\nThese films received acclaim for their storytelling, direction, and the psychological tension they built throughout their narratives.",
